a) was causing teens to suicide<br>
b) was addictive<br>
c) was somehow associated with devil worship<br>
<br>
I played in a dungeon for 3 of 4 years and graduated with honours. The Dungeonmaster flunked out. Was the game to blame? From the outside it would be easy to say yes. But in reality he freely admitted he would have played some other game just as obsessively if D&amp;D did not exist.<br>
<br>
I went on to become for a while a workaholic. Alright, running your own business in the computer field makes you susceptible to this. Was the computer to blame? No, it took me to recognize the symptoms &lt;inability to tell a customer no at 9pm Sunday eve&gt;. and address them. Cant blame anything but myself.<br>
<br>
If I choose to spend some of my leisure time playing eq,  &lt;and my noons and breaks reading boards LOL&gt;, as an adult I take full responsibility for my choices. Am I addicted? Maybe. Is this addiction harmful to me? Well, I should spend more hours at the gym and less on EQ for a better lifestyle, but at least I now drink herbal tea while playing. On the other hand when I have a day at work where I feel like killing something I can do so in a socially accepted way. <br>
<br>
Is this addiction harmful to my family? The kids are at an age where Mom is the local teleporting druid more than a valued party member. The husband values the baking skill I level in, but marriage to a gnome means that he has also an intimate relationship ongoing with a couple of big block engines and a transmission or two.<br>
<br>
I value the game for it ability to connect me with like minded people of all ages. I find the average mean intelligence and literacy level of the EQ player above the norm in the population &lt;some trolls excepted&gt;. The addiction factor for me is that I find friends in the game, and I like to spend my time with people. Without EQ, I would spend the hours reading, trying yet a new strategy on Civilization, or mucking around on my truck &lt; and gleefully putting the tools back in the box where above gnome cannot find them &gt;.<br>
<br>
Could I give it up? Of course! Done it lots of times!<br>
